 You notice that you are able to control what happens in the movie, and you start manipulating things for your own amusement. You make yourself send random e-mails to people you know in this new life. It's innocent enough. The others don't seem to have the same control. They don't notice that you do. 

You make him then start googling how to bring a former reincarnation of you back to life. He sees that a therapist may be able to help. You send him to the therapist. The therapist does a hypnosis session, and the former you remembers everything. They are overwhelmed but you keep them under control. You have them ask to bring back you specifically. They are told it is possible, but difficult. They say they don't even ethically think they should. You have your new self insist. 
They go back into hypnosis, and you are brought back to life.
 You take over and replace them. You are eager to see what you have been missing, but the whole process has exhausted you. You go home to rest. You wake up, excited to start your fresh new life. However, you spend this life second guessing yourself. Are your decisions your own or is

 You notice that you are able to control what happens in the movie, and you start manipulating things for your own amusement. You make yourself send random e-mails to people you know in this new life. It's innocent enough. The others don't seem to have the same control. They don't notice that you do. 

You make him then start googling how to bring a former reincarnation of you back to life. He sees that a therapist may be able to help. You send him to the therapist. The therapist does a hypnosis session, and the former you remembers everything. They are overwhelmed but you keep them under control. You have them ask to bring back you specifically. They are told it is possible, but difficult. They say they don't even ethically think they should. You have your new self insist. 
They go back into hypnosis, and you are brought back to life.
 You take over and replace them. You are eager to see what you have been missing, but the whole process has exhausted you. You go home to rest. You wake up, excited to start your fresh new life. However, you spend this life second guessing yourself. Are your decisions your own or is someone else controlling them? You begin to get paranoid.

 You notice that you are able to control what happens in the movie, and you start manipulating things for your own amusement. You make yourself send random e-mails to people you know in this new life. It's innocent enough. The others don't seem to have the same control. They don't notice that you do. 

You make him then start googling how to bring a former reincarnation of you back to life. He sees that a therapist may be able to help. You send him to the therapist. The therapist does a hypnosis session, and the former you remembers everything. They are overwhelmed but you keep them under control. You have them ask to bring back you specifically. They are told it is possible, but difficult. They say they don't even ethically think they should. You have your new self insist. 
They go back into hypnosis, and you are brought back to life.
 You take over and replace them. You are eager to see what you have been missing, but the whole process has exhausted you. You go home to rest. You wake up, excited to start your fresh new life. However, you spend this life second guessing yourself. Are your decisions your own or is someone else controlling them? You begin to get paranoid.

In the movie you see yourself walking around a big city, and then sitting down in front of a computer.
 You notice that you are able to control what happens in the movie, and you start manipulating things for your own amusement. You make yourself send random e-mails to people you know in this new life. It's innocent enough. The others don't seem to have the same control. They don't notice that you do. 

You make him then start googling how to bring a former reincarnation of you back to life. He sees that a therapist may be able to help. You send him to the therapist. The therapist does a hypnosis session, and the former you remembers everything. They are overwhelmed but you keep them under control. You have them ask to bring back you specifically. They are told it is possible, but difficult. They say they don't even ethically think they should. You have your new self insist. 
They go back into hypnosis, and you are brought back to life.
 You take over and replace them. You are eager to see what you have been missing, but the whole process has exhausted you. You go home to rest. You wake up, excited to start your fresh new life. However, you spend this life second guessing yourself. Are your decisions your own or is someone else controlling them? You begin to get paranoid.
